  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 27 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 940 mg
course: main course
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/truffled-mushroom-flatbreads-5cf148a58b02f000105e2832
author: HelloFresh
time required: 25 minutes
---

Place a foil-lined #baking sheet{} (2 sheets for 4 servings) in #oven{}; preheat to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @baby portobello mushrooms{8%ounce}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}. Cut @lemon{1} into wedges.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms, shallot, and half the @Italian seasoning{1%teaspoon}. Cook, stirring, until browned and softened, about ~{10%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Remove preheated baking sheet from oven and place @flatbreads{2} on it. (For 4 servings, divide between both sheets.) Top with @Italian cheese blend{1%cup}, remaining Italian seasoning, and mushroom mixture. Season with salt and pepper.

Bake flatbreads until cheese is melted and crust is golden, ~{7-9%minutes}. (For 4 servings, swap rack positions halfway through baking.) Remove from oven, then drizzle with @truffle oil{5%teaspoon} to taste.

> TIP: Start with a few drops and add more from there—you may not use all the oil.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss @arugula{2%ounce} with a drizzle of olive oil and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Cut flatbreads into slices. Serve with salad on the side.

> TIP: If you like, you can top your flatbreads with the salad instead.